passage:
The speeder Rogue Three races around one of the giant
     walker's feet, trailing the cable behind it. Continuing
     around the back foot, Rogue Three then circles the walker
     around the tail end.

75

Wedge checks his controls and banks around the front of the
     walker.

                         WEDGE
               One more pass.

                         JANSON
               Coming around. Once more.

76

The speeder sweeps left to right in front of the giant legs,
     towing the cable behind it.

77

JANSON
               Once more.

     Wedge swings the speeder between the legs of the giant
     walker.

                            JANSON (CONTâ€™D)
               Cable out!     Let her go!

                         WEDGE
               Detach cable.

78

The cable release on the back of the speeder snaps loose and
     the cable drops away.

79

The speeder zooms away into the distance. The tangled legs
     of the enormous war machine attempt a step, but as they do
     the giant Imperial walker begins to topple. It teeters for
     a moment, and then crashes onto the icy ground, sending snow
     and metal pieces flying.

81

The troops in the trenches cheer at the sight of the
     crashing walker.

     An officer gives a signal to his men and Rebel troops charge
     the fallen war machine.

                           TRENCH OFFICER
                Come on!

     The troops run toward the downed walker, followed by two
     Rebel speeders flying overhead. Just as they reach the
     walker, it explodes, the impact throwing some of the men
     onto the frozen ground.

82

Wedge lets out a triumphant yell, banking his speeder away
     from the fallen walker.

                          WEDGE
                    (into comlink)
                Whooha! That got him!

83

LUKE
                    (into comlink)
                I see it, Wedge. Good work.

84
